'''Taste Confusion Matrix (TCM)''' is a method in which many compounds are tested at the same time.  It is a study of human [[taste]] [[perception]].  It characterizes the quality of taste with identification patterns of some 10 stimuli which are analyzed.<ref>Hettinger T. P., Gent J. F., Marks L. E., Frank M. E. (November 1999). "[https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10598466 A confusion matrix for the study of taste perception]". ''Percept Psychophys'' '''61''' (8).</ref>

